This paper is about recommendation systems, which typically fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The use of Factorization Machines (FM) and knowledge graphs also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of semantic features, which are often used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and knowledge representation (cs.DB).
